 class=\"review-body\">Until a theme I was using required the installation of Otter Blocks Gutenberg confused the heck out of me. Way to go!</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Handy Gutenberg widgets</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/rstar1web\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/2703e7ad43f33055067c70951faaf193?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/2703e7ad43f33055067c70951faaf193?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/rstar1web\" class=\"reviewer-name\">rstar1web</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">December 6, 2018</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Really new add-in that adds functional blocks to Gutenberg. Allows Gutenberg editor without going into page builders - simplifies any edits for my clients.  I\'ve only used a couple of blocks so far, but they are pretty nicely designed and configurable.</div>\n</div>\n\";}s:17:\"short_description\";s:159:\"Create beautiful and attracting posts, pages, and landing pages with Gutenberg Blocks and Template Library by Otter. Otter comes with dozens of Gutenb &hellip;\";s:13:\"download_link\";s:55:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/otter-blocks.zip